# Node Backend Rules

## Runtime & style
- Follow existing module system in repo (ESM/CommonJS). Do not mix styles in same area.
- Use async/await over raw Promise chains where practical.
- Validate input at boundaries (HTTP handlers, queue consumers, cron jobs).

## API/handlers
- Keep handlers thin: parse/validate -> call service -> map response.
- Put business logic in service/domain layer, not directly in route/controller.
- Return consistent error objects/status codes according to existing patterns.

## Errors & logging
- Never swallow errors.
- Include actionable context in logs, but never log secrets/PII.
- Prefer structured logs if project already uses them.

## Data access
- Reuse existing data access patterns (repository/service/db client).
- Avoid N+1 style query loops when batching is possible.
- Keep transactions explicit where needed.

## Tests
- Add/update tests for changed behavior.
- Cover:
  - happy path
  - one relevant failure path
- Do not rewrite unrelated tests.

## Performance & reliability
- Avoid blocking operations in request path.
- Add timeouts/retries only where existing architecture supports it.
